e</strong>, 2ª colocada no Festival Megazine do Jornal O Globo; <strong>The Fraktal</strong>, aliando o peso dos instrumentos analógicos com melodias e calmas e dançantes de sintetizadores e teclados; <strong>Kapitu</strong>, com seu rock oitentista e a mistura de ritmos brasileiros da <strong>Bow Bow Cogumelo</strong>.\r\n\r\nAlém dos shows, apresentações dos <strong>DJs Mario MOPTOP e Uno</strong>; intervenções artísticas de alunos da Escola Nacional de Circo; exposição de fotos do Grito Rock RJ 2010 e de obras de duas feras dos quadrinhos: o carioca <strong>Latuff</strong> e suas ilustrações de cunho crítico e o paulista <strong>Márcio Baraldi</strong>, apresentando divertidos cartuns roqueiros.\r\n\r\n<strong>E para você que tem banda, compareça! Iniciativas como esta prestigiam a cena independente e a sua presença é importante para que cada vez mais possamos ocupar esse espaco criando novas oportunidades para a sua banda tocar!</strong>\r\n\r\n——————————————\r\n<h3>TNB NA RUA</h3>\r\nO TNB na rua é mais uma iniciativa TNB que visa gerar ambientes de networking para você e sua banda! Agora, além de se conectar aqui na internet, essa é uma oportunidade para conhecer e se apresentar para quem faz os eventos dentro do TNB, por isso é legal levar seu material promocional : CD, demo, adesivo ou cartão de visitas!\r\n<h3>PRODUTOR DA VEZ</h3>\r\nNesse evento você vai ter oportunidade de conhecer os produtores do Circuito Fora do Eixo, uma rede de mais de 70 coletivos culturais responsáveis por vários eventos e projetos culturais espalhados por todo o Brasil, e de conhecer o projeto “Grito Rock”, maior festival integrado da América Latina.\r\n\r\n<strong>Aproveite a balada, entre em contato com os produtores e faça a sua banda acontecer!</strong>\r\n\r\n——————————————\r\n<h3>SERVIÇO</h3>\r\n<strong>Evento: Grito Rock no Circo Voador</strong>\r\nDia: 24/3\r\nLocal: <a href=\"http://www.circovoador.com.br/\" target=\"_blank\">Circo Voador</a> – Rua dos Arcos, s/nº – Lapa – Rio de Janeiro – RJ\r\nHorário: 20 horas\r\nShows: Emicida + Macaco Bong, Vivendo do Ócio, Holger, Tereza, Medulla e Cabrones Sarnentos.\r\nProdutor responsável: Fora do Eixo RJ – Saiba mais: <a href=\"http://ponteplural.com.br/\" target=\"_blank\">Ponte Plura</a> | <a href=\"http://ow.ly/4jz7X\" target=\"_blank\">Perfil TNB :: Música Fora do Eixo</a>\r\nInformações: <a href=\"http://www.gritorockrj.com.br/\" target=\"_blank\">Grito Rock RJ</a>\r\nIngresso: R$ 40,00 (inteira) e R$ 20,00 (meia-entrada) – <em>Meia-entrada para quem levar 1kg de alimento não perecível, estudantes e maiores de 60 anos, mediante apresentação dos respectivos documentos comprobatórios</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Evento: Grito Rock Niteroi</strong>\r\nDia: 25/3\r\nLocal: Campus da UFF no Gragoatá, Bloco E – Rua Marquês do Paraná, nº 100, Centro, Niterói\r\nHorário: 18 horas\r\nShows: Holger, Tipo Uísque, Colombia Coffee, The Fraktal, Kapitu e Bow Bow Cogumelo\r\nProdutor responsável: Fora do Eixo RJ – Saiba mais: <a href=\"http://ponteplural.com.br/\" target=\"_blank\">Ponte Plura</a> | <a href=\"http://ow.ly/4jz7X\" target=\"_blank\">Perfil TNB :: Música Fora do Eixo</a>\r\nInformações: <a href=\"http://www.gritorockrj.com.br/\" target=\"_blank\">Grito Rock RJ</a>\r\nIngresso: 1 kg de alimento não perecível para as vítimas das enchentes da região serrana\r\n\r\nEsperamos vocês lá!\r\n<strong>Toque no Brasil ! Toque em todo lugar!</strong>\r\n\r\nEquipe TNB\r\n<a href=\"http://ow.ly/4jzn5\" target=\"_blank\">O TNB com a sua cara!</a>\r\n\r\n</div>','tnb na rua :: venha conhecer o universo tnb no grito rock rio de janeiro','','inherit','open','open','','244-revision-6','','','2011-03-24 14:12:10','2011-03-24 14:12:10','',244,'http://localhost/tnbranch/2011/03/24/244-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(252,1,'2011-03-24 14:13:24','2011-03-24 14:13:24','<h2 id=\"anonymous_element_61\">GRITO ROCK 2011 – THE LARGEST INTEGRATED FESTIVAL OF THE AMERICAS COMES TO THE U.S.</h2>\r\n<a rel=\"attachment wp-att-19183\" href=\"http://localhost/tnbranch/?attachment_id=19183\"><img title=\"GR-NY\" src=\"http://toquenobrasil-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/GR-NY-400x600.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"360\" height=\"540\" /></a>\r\n\r\nGrito Rock, an independent Brazilian music festival series produced by a network of collaborators, will feature its first U.S. event on Wednesday, March 23, 2011 at <a href=\"http://www.pianosnyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Pianos</strong></a> with an 8 p.m. performance by <a href=\"http://www.constantina.art.br/index_eng.html\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Constantina</strong></a>. In its ninth year, the festival is being hosted in 132 cities—an increase of 65% over the previous year—and establishing itself as one of the largest integrated events on the planet. This time the festival reaches the borders of Latin America, embracing 10 different countries: Brazil, United States of America, Argentina, Uruguay, Bolivia, Chile, Panama, Costa Rica, Honduras and El Salvador.\r\n\r\nFor the first time since it’s been held in a collaborative manner, Grito Rock will happen in all 27 states in Brazil plus eight other countries, including cities in Central, South and North America, with 51% of the participating cities part of Grito Rock for the first time.\r\n\r\nThe idea of promoting a festival within the network’s layouts goes beyond stimulating cultural growth and production. According to the National Manager of Grito Rock 2011, Felipe Altenfelder, “Grito is primarily a way to stimulate the connections, the circulation of artists, distribution and marketing of products, integrated communications, training of new and old cultural agents, and the generation, evolution and dissemination of social-work management technologies.” To encourage this whole exchange, organizers launched the Grito Rock Campaigns, all tools of mobilization and integration in many different areas.\r\n\r\nDespite the “rock” term in the name, it does not restrict musical styles in the multiple lineups. A pioneer among the organizers of the festival, Marielle Ramirez, says that “when we started, rock was the fuel and aesthetic chosen by those who thought they could make a difference, but over time we all began to understand that the “rock” word in the name was a matter of attitude, and not a genre, so the sound could be of any kind” referring to the “do it yourself” motto, which was born in punk rock culture and has been adapted to “do it together” in the independent movement that produce events such as Grito Rock.\r\n\r\nMusic has always been the major attraction, but lately, it shares space with other art segments. Lectures, debates and workshops take place in the Circuito Fora do Eixo (Off-Axis Circuit) since 2007. Starting this year, “Grito Acts” was created to occupy the scene with scenic tours, visiting six cities in Minas Gerais and Sao Paulo in July. Another campaign that began in 2011 is the Social-Environmental Fora do Eixo which will take account of the impact that the festival causes in the environment and promote the planting of seedlings in three regions of different biomes in Brazil.\r\n\r\nGrito Rock is an accomplishment of <a href=\"http://foradoeixo.org.br/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Circuito Fora do Eixo</strong></a>, a network of collaborative and decentralized actions, consisting of 72 points in 26 states of Brazil that share free technology to produce culture and social change.\r\n\r\nGrito Rock Festival’s 2011 edition used <a href=\"http://toquenobrasil.com.br/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>TNB</strong></a> to choose the headline for all 130 events that integrated the festival, adding up to 1000 selected bands. TNB is the first Latin American music opportunities social network, and it’s goal is to connect artists, festivals, venues, producers and brands in a digital platform that allows and increases business possibilities. Check it out: <a href=\"http://toquenobrasil.com.br/\" target=\"_blank\">www.toquenobrasil.com.br</a>\r\n\r\n<a rel=\"attachment wp-att-19182\" href=\"http://localhost/tnbranch/?attachment_id=19182\"><img title=\"TNB_site\" src=\"http://toquenobrasil-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/TNB_site20.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"472\" height=\"64\" /></a>','GRITO ROCK 2011 – THE LARGEST INTEGRATED FESTIVAL OF THE AMERICAS COMES TO THE US','','publish','open','open','','grito-rock-2011-%e2%80%93-the-largest-integrated-festival-of-the-americas-comes-to-the-us','','','2011-03-24 14:13:56','2011-03-24 14:13:56','',0,'http://localhost/tnbranch/?p=252',0,'post','',0),(253,1,'2011-03-24 14:13:06','2011-03-24 14:13:06','','GRITO ROCK 2011 – THE LARGEST INTEGRATED FESTIVAL OF THE AMERICAS COMES TO THE US','','inherit','open','open','','252-revision','','','2011-03-24 14:13:06','2011-03-24 14:13:06','',252,'http://localhost/tnbranch/2011/03/24/252-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(255,1,'2011-03-24 14:13:24','2011-03-24 14:13:24','<h2 id=\"anonymous_element_61\">GRITO ROCK 2011 – THE LARGEST INTEGRATED FESTIVAL OF THE AMERICAS COMES TO THE U.S.</h2>\r\n<a rel=\"attachment wp-att-19183\" href=\"http://localhost/tnbranch/?attachment_id=19183\"><img title=\"GR-NY\" src=\"http://toquenobrasil-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/GR-NY-400x600.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"360\" height=\"540\" /></a>\r\n\r\nGrito Rock, an independent Brazilian music festival series produced by a network of collaborators, will feature its first U.S. event on Wednesday, March 23, 2011 at <a href=\"http://www.pianosnyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Pianos</strong></a> with an 8 p.m. performance by <a href=\"http://www.constantina.art.br/index_eng.html\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Constantina</strong></a>. In its ninth year, the festival is being hosted in 132 cities—an increase of 65% over the previous year—and establishing itself as one of the largest integrated events on the planet. This time the festival reaches the borders of Latin America, embracing 10 different countri