rong>Circuito Fora do Eixo</strong></a>, a network of collaborative and decentralized actions, consisting of 72 points in 26 states of Brazil that share free technology to produce culture and social change.\r\n\r\nGrito Rock Festival’s 2011 edition used <a href=\"http://toquenobrasil.com.br/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>TNB</strong></a> to choose the headline for all 130 events that integrated the festival, adding up to 1000 selected bands. TNB is the first Latin American music opportunities social network, and it’s goal is to connect artists, festivals, venues, producers and brands in a digital platform that allows and increases business possibilities. Check it out: <a href=\"http://toquenobrasil.com.br/\" target=\"_blank\">www.toquenobrasil.com.br</a>\r\n\r\n<a rel=\"attachment wp-att-19182\" href=\"http://localhost/tnbranch/?attachment_id=19182\"><img title=\"TNB_site\" src=\"http://toquenobrasil-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/TNB_site20.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"472\" height=\"64\" /></a>','GRITO ROCK 2011 – THE LARGEST INTEGRATED FESTIVAL OF THE AMERICAS COMES TO THE US','','inherit','open','open','','252-revision-4','','','2011-03-24 14:13:56','2011-03-24 14:13:56','',252,'http://localhost/tnbranch/2011/03/24/252-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(257,1,'2011-03-24 14:14:58','2011-03-24 14:14:58','<h2 id=\"anonymous_element_61\">GRITO ROCK 2011 – THE LARGEST INTEGRATED FESTIVAL OF THE AMERICAS COMES TO THE U.S.</h2>\n<a rel=\"attachment wp-att-19183\" href=\"http://localhost/tnbranch/?attachment_id=19183\"><img title=\"GR-NY\" src=\"http://toquenobrasil-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/GR-NY-400x600.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"360\" height=\"540\" /></a>\n\nGrito Rock, an independent Brazilian music festival series produced by a network of collaborators, will feature its first U.S. event on Wednesday, March 23, 2011 at <a href=\"http://www.pianosnyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Pianos</strong></a> with an 8 p.m. performance by 